    <div class="hero">
      <div class="hero-card">
        <h1>Urban Air Quality — Cleaned & Analyzed</h1>
        <p class="subtitle">This one‑pager summarizes the cleaning and analysis of an air quality dataset containing trace gases (CO, NOx, NO₂) and meteorological factors (temperature, relative humidity, absolute humidity). We removed invalid readings (−200), imputed missing numeric values, and built a unified time index for robust analysis.</p>
        <div class="meta">
          <span class="badge" title="Data rows">N = 9,357</span>
          <span class="badge">Period: multi‑season</span>
          <span class="badge">Theme: Academic · Purple</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h2 id="abstract">Abstract</h2>
        <p>We process an atmospheric dataset by (i) removing sentinel values (−200), (ii) imputing missing numeric entries with mean values, and (iii) constructing a <em>DateTime</em> field from <em>Date</em> and <em>Time</em>. Descriptive statistics indicate moderate CO, highly variable NOx with extreme peaks, and stable yet non‑trivial NO₂ concentrations. Meteorological variables span all seasons, enabling analysis of weather–pollution interactions.</p>
        <div class="note">Keywords: air quality, data cleaning, imputation, CO, NOx, NO₂, temperature, humidity, urban environment.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <section id="data" aria-labelledby="data">
      <div class="grid three">
        <div class="card">
          <h2>Dataset</h2>
          <p><strong>File:</strong> <code>AirQuality.csv</code></p>
          <p><strong>Observations:</strong> 9,357 after cleaning</p>
          <p><strong>Variables:</strong> CO(GT), NOx(GT), NO₂(GT), T, RH, AH, sensors (PT08.S*)</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Invalid readings coded as <code>−200</code> → treated as missing</li>
            <li>Trailing empty columns removed</li>
            <li>Time index created from Date + Time</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h2>Cleaning Steps</h2>
          <ol>
            <li>Drop unnamed columns</li>
            <li>Replace <code>−200</code> with <code>NaN</code></li>
            <li>Impute numeric columns with column means</li>
            <li>Construct <code>DateTime</code> using <code>%d/%m/%Y %H.%M.%S</code></li>
            <li>Drop unparsable timestamps; reset index</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h2>At‑a‑Glance</h2>
          <div class="kpis">
            <div class="kpi"><span class="label">CO mean</span><span class="value">2.15 mg/m³</span></div>
            <div class="kpi"><span class="label">NOx mean</span><span class="value">246.90 ppb</span></div>
            <div class="kpi"><span class="label">NO₂ mean</span><span class="value">113.09 ppb</span></div>
            <div class="kpi"><span class="label">Temp mean</span><span class="value">18.32 °C</span></div>
            <div class="kpi"><span class="label">RH mean</span><span class="value">49.23 %</span></div>
            <div class="kpi"><span class="label">AH mean</span><span class="value">1.03</span></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="methods">
      <div class="grid two">
        <div class="card">
          <h2>Methods</h2>
          <p><strong>Imputation:</strong> Column‑wise mean for numeric variables, preserving scale and variance for descriptive analysis.</p>
          <p><strong>Time Series Setup:</strong> <code>DateTime</code> used as index for ordering and potential seasonality checks.</p>
          <p><strong>Descriptives:</strong> Count, mean, standard deviation, and range computed for core variables.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h2>Reproducible Code (Python)</h2>
<pre><code>import pandas as pd, numpy as np

# Load & tidy
df = pd.read_csv('AirQuality.csv', sep=';', decimal=',', encoding='latin1')
df = df.loc[:, ~df.columns.str.contains('^Unnamed')]
df = df.replace(-200, np.nan)

# Impute numeric
for c in df.select_dtypes(include=[np.number]):
    df[c] = df[c].fillna(df[c].mean())

# DateTime
df = df.dropna(subset=['Date','Time'])
df['DateTime'] = pd.to_datetime(
    df['Date'] + ' ' + df['Time'],
    format='%d/%m/%Y %H.%M.%S', errors='coerce')
df = df.dropna(subset=['DateTime']).reset_index(drop=True)
</code></pre>
          <div class="note">Swap the imputation strategy (e.g., median or KNN) if distributional robustness is a priority.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

