    <section id="findings">
      <div class="grid two">
        <div class="card">
          <h2>Key Findings</h2>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>NOx variability</strong> is high with extreme peaks (up to 1,479 ppb), reflecting episodic emissions (e.g., traffic or industry).</li>
            <li><strong>CO levels</strong> are moderate on average (≈2.15 mg/m³) but exhibit short‑term spikes.</li>
            <li><strong>NO₂</strong> remains comparatively stable yet indicates persistent urban pollution.</li>
            <li><strong>Meteorology</strong> spans full seasons (−1.9 to 44.6 °C; 9–89% RH), enabling weather–pollution analysis.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h2>Next Steps</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>Time‑of‑day and day‑of‑week patterns for traffic‑related pollutants</li>
            <li>Meteorology‑adjusted models (e.g., GAMs, random forests)</li>
            <li>Anomaly detection for extreme NOx episodes</li>
            <li>Alternative imputations (median/KNN) for robustness checks</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
